JOHANNESBURG - Four men escaped after robbing a shop owner at gunpoint at the China-Mart Mall in Crown Mines.  Police confirmed the four men held up the owner of a store in the mall and stole a substantial amount of cash and his iPhone before fleeing the scene. READ: Three wounded as Kyalami mall on lockdown The men reportedly shot twice into the air as they left in two vehicles. One of the vehicles used to escape was a white VW, witnesses were unsure whether it was a Jetta or Passat make. SAPS pursued the men in a high-speed chase; they were able to evade pursuit after they discarded the stolen cellphone, which police had been tracking. No one was arrested and no injuries were reported.  eNCA